A FBSS will still give 21% haste to any weapon regardless how good that weapon is, at lv51 or lv60.<br>
It will still be much better compared to having no haste item at all.<br>
<br>
A focus2 dmg item will not work at all with lv49 nukes or higher.<br>
It will not be better than no focus item at all.<br>
It will do nothing.<br>
A lv60 wizard will use lv60 nukes like sunstrike.<br>
Lv44 nukes will not do more dmg even if he has all types of focus2 items equipped. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/urombusmindspire.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rombus Mindspire</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><table width=111><tr><td style=filter:glow(color=#6633FF strength=1);font-family:arial;font-weight;bold;font-size:'1pt' nowrap><font size=1 color=#FFFFFF face=Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif>Forum Moderator</font></td></tr></table><table width=111><tr><td style=filter:glow(color=#6633FF strength=1);font-family:arial;font-weight;bold;font-size:'1pt' nowrap><font size=1 color=#FFFFFF face=Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif>Verant's #1 Fanboy</font></td></tr></table><br><table width=111><tr><td style=filter:glow(color=#6633FF strength=1);font-family:arial;font-weight;bold;font-size:'1pt' nowrap><font size=1 color=#FFFFFF face=Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif><a href=mailto:rombus@graffe.com style=text-decoration: none><font color=#FFFFFF>Contact Rombus</font></a></font></td></tr></table></span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/14/02 8:14:14 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1191.topic&index=141>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.tritonguild.com/rombus/sidepic.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I wish...</span><hr size=1> Ok, and a level 55 Warrior vs. a Froglok Krup Knight with only a FBSS as his haste will suck compared to when he was level 40 vs. a Froglok Guk Knight with only a FBSS as his haste.  <br>
<br>
A Wizard, however, may lose the ability to use his level II focus item at 55 but if he has a level III focus item he'll be getting the same benifits as if he was level 40 using a level II focus item - they're both +20%.<br>
<br>
To put it simpler, a level 55 Warrior using the same FBSS he has been for the past 15 levels will benifit about as much from it as a level 55 Wizard using a level II focus item.  While you can't use your level II focus item that FBSS is virtually useless to him.  Hope that helps. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=ervonz>Ervonz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/14/02 8:47:38 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1191.topic&index=142>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I wish...</span><hr size=1> I agree and understand your point.<br>
A lv55 warrior with a FBSS will not be very good compared to someone with better equipment.<br>
And a lv55 warrior needs better haste. A FBSS is not good enough.<br>
<br>
But what I´m saying is also true.<br>
A FBSS will always be better compared to having no haste item at all.<br>
Because if the lv55 warrior had no haste item at all he would be much worse.<br>
<br>
So I guess we are both right.<br>
<br>
